description:
Related to #300985 (backend).

Replace the axios call for recent boards in `app/assets/javascripts/boards/components/boards_selector.vue` using the following GraphQL query (more details in the issue linked above).

```
query fetchRecentProjectBoards {
  project(fullPath: "gitlab-org/gitlab") {
    recentIssueBoards {
      edges {
        node {
          name
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Problem

Pipeline Graph for multi-project pipeline is a premium feature, however, it is available in ~"GitLab Free".  

## Solution

The code block below needs to be added to GraphQL to ensure that the Pipeline Graph for multi-project pipeline remains a premium feature.

```
{
  project(fullPath: "root/downstream-pipeline-project") {
    pipeline(iid: "37") {
      user {
        namespace {
          actualPlan{
            paid <- THIS is a boolean that will return if a user is in a paid/free tier.
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```
